HEADWORD: Zirconic
<hw>Zir*con"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, containing, or resembling, zirconium; <as>as,
<ex>zirconic</ex> oxide; <ex>zirconic</ex> compounds.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Zirconic acid</b></col>, <cd>an acid of zirconium
analogous to carbonic and silicic acids, known only in its
salts.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zirconium</ent>⟦br⟧
